      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Originalism is a constitutional theory that insists the text of the Constitution should be interpreted according to its original public meaning at the time of enactment. Proponents argue this method preserves the democratic will of the founding generation and prevents judges from imposing their own personal policy preferences under the guise of interpretation. By anchoring legal decisions in fixed historical facts rather than evolving social values, originalism ensures that the Constitution remains a stable, predictable framework for governance. This approach is essential for maintaining the rule of law and preventing the judiciary from acting as a super-legislature that overrides the choices of elected representatives.",
